POLOKWANE – Following a week of highs in the thirties and sunny conditions, lower temperatures and rain will bring some relief to the City of Stars. Thunderstorms are predicted for every day of the week, according to AccuWeather’s forecast, along with humid conditions. The probability of thundershowers will range between 40%-77% this week with rain expected in the mornings and evenings.  Monday to Thursday (January 30-February 2) will see temperatures between 24ºC to 27ºC with partly cloudy conditions, while the weekend will range from 27ºC to 23ºC. More rain is expected going into the weekend with a 66% of thundershowers on Thursday (February 2) and a 77% chance on Friday (February 3).  The probability of rain will continue into next week. 